1.title: Solace
1.plot: A man consumed with grief over the murder of his partner, returns to the site of her murder as its the only place he can find solace.

2.title: The Hard Decision
2.plot: Split personality disorder consumes a man as he debates with himself on whether or not he should seek professional help.

3.title: I'm Not a Rat
3.plot: A mafia enforcer contemplates his options - A future to look forward to... Or his honor.

4.title: Return to Me
4.plot: Returning to the station she departed, a man waits in the hope that his lost love will return to rekindle what they once had.

5.title: Come on Carl
5.plot: Monroe (Dan Hill) is a cocky undercover cop who is fast losing track of the line between cop and criminal. Carl (Ben Grimshaw), his handler notices the change and lectures him on his professionalism.

6.title: When Push Comes to Kill
6.plot: After an altercation at a nightclub, Murray (Daniel Hill) and Dyl (Ben Grimshaw) accidentally kill an anonymous stranger. They dispose the body at a work site Dyl is working on in hopes of concealing the deed. The two are conflicted about the situation and their differing opinions clash.

7.title: A Final Skype
7.plot: A Journalist is sheltered in a safe house with his cameraman Scott. They have witnessed violations of human rights in a village just outside of Kudat in Azerbaijan.

8.title: For You My Son
8.plot: A man entertains his son with his favourite puppet "Oscar" to make him happy.

9.title: The Private Investigator
9.plot: A private eye has lost track of his own life, transfixed upon the very people he follows.

10.title: The Phone Number
10.plot: A group of hungover housemates try recapping the previous night's party, and eventually fight over who gets the lovely Jesse's phone number.

11.title: Drifter - Part 1
11.plot: On a cold winters night a troubled man (Dan Hill) swallows his pride and calls his mother whom he hasn't contacted in 10 years.

12.title: That Awkward Moment
12.plot: An awkward interaction between old school friends at their friend's 30th birthday party leads to tension.

13.title: A Prank Goes South
13.plot: Two housemates (Mike Salisbury + Dan Hill) start discussing their financial difficulties when they decide to play a practical joke on their other friend and house mate Tristan (Michael Corcoran).

14.title: Texan Vampire - Part 1
14.plot: A nomad vampire, far from his home of Texas, after one hundred years of wandering he struggles to cope with his affliction and the loss of the innocent lives he must take to survive.

15.title: Retribution
15.plot: A man (Dan Hill) is hell bent on retribution against Ryan, (Tim Grimshaw) whom he suspects to be responsible for the hit and run of his one true love.

16.title: Death Finds Us All
16.plot: A man (Michael Corcoran) has a strange encounter with a mysterious stranger (Dan Hill) in a park late one night.

17.title: Custody Problems
17.plot: A man tries to seek help via a mental health helpline regarding the custody of his son.

18.title: Jersey Shore Depression
18.plot: A troubled man (Michael Corcoran) faces the reality of modern society and tries to 'escape' it but a pedestrian walking by (Dan Hill) sees and attempts to talk him out of it.

19.title: Mums Mystery Boyfriend
19.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who comes home to find that his Mother (Naomi Lisner) has started dating again, the only problem is it's with his best friend (Michael De Martino).

20.title: Awkward Audition
20.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who is auditioning for a role in a film, he is greeted by an eccentric director (Michael De Martino) and his producer (Naomi Lisner) who look to see how far an actor will go for his role.

21.title: Cold Feet
21.plot: Two professional bank robbers (Dan Hill and Justin Brewster), argue about their next job and whether or not they should see it through.

22.title: Texan Vampire - Part 2
22.plot: The nomadic vampire (Dan Hill) returns, as he contemplates a return to his home of Texas. His hunger increases as he avoids the inevitable and continues to cope with the trauma of having to take the lives of innocent people just to survive.

23.title: Introducing Benny Kirkright
23.plot: Benny Kirkright (Daniel Hill) decides to blow everyone's mind with his intensity as he auditions for Big Brother 2012.

24.title: Foul Deeds
24.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man driving around at night looking for his next victim.

25.title: Breakdown
25.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who is stranded in the wilderness miles away from the nearest town. He reflects upon his situation and his life up until this point.

26.title: Come Home
26.plot: Daniel Hill and Cassandra Campbell-Smith star as a brother and sister, who have grown distant after their troublesome past.

27.title: A Charitable Man
27.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who answers his door to a local preacher (Michael Corcoran).

28.title: Losing Control
28.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man suffering from mental illness who tries to illicit a sexual relationship with his carer (Cassandra Campbell-Smith)

29.title: Is This Really Happening?
29.plot: A man (Dan Hill) on a strange late night stroll runs from his past and the line blurs between reality and whats in his head..

30.title: Drifter - Part 2
30.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a troubled young man who has decided to hitch hike his way back home. Left feeling abandoned and unwanted in the world he desperately searches for some purpose to keep walking down that dirt road.

31.title: Bennys Revenge
31.plot: The intensity of Benny Kirkright (Daniel Hill) returns as he is disappointed he missed out on the opportunity to blow everyone's mind on Big Brother 2012.

32.title: Sobriety
32.plot: Dan Hill stars as a recovered junkie who returns to his old hang out, conflicted by his past and the challenge of staying clean he explores the nature of his sobriety and the relationships he once had with people that have now been severed.

33.title: A World Too Damaged
33.plot: Daniel Hill stars as Josh, a young man struggling to come to terms with a frightening new world, the world after a zombie apocalypse. He complains about the compassion and carelessness of the people he is forced to survive with, realising that only one thing matters now and that's survival.

34.title: The Jenkins Six
34.plot: Daniel Hill stars as Sean Jenkins frontman for the famous Jenkins 6. Sean shares perhaps a little too much about the band and his personal life..

35.title: The Effects of Bullying
35.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who lingers around his former School's playground reminiscing on the scars left from the bullying of his classmates.

36.title: Prisoner of a New World
36.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man forced into slavery after an alien invasion, he has nothing to do but work and reflect upon his situation late at night in his prison.

37.title: Dennis' True Love
37.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man grief stricken by the break up with his one true love.

38.title: Lifestyle Landscaping
38.plot: Daniel Hill stars as Landscaping king pin Damon Hill, as he discusses the short comings of his new apprentice.

39.title: Freedom Beyond the Border
39.plot: Daniel Hill stars as an American pilot who has been imprisoned after being shot down over Nazi Germany, he has escaped and is trying to cross the border to France and seek help with the resistance.

40.title: Drifter - Part 3
40.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a troubled young man who has traveled across the country to return home to confront his parents. With little money and just the clothes on his back he has been struggling along on in his journey, reflecting as he is so close to being home.

41.title: A Warning to the Jury
41.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a mob enforcer leaning on a juror (Laura Vine) trying to threaten her into helping his friend get off.

42.title: The Under Shout
42.plot: Mark (Michael Corcoran) comes home to find his eccentric neighbour Kesler (Isaac Still) on his bed. His conversation about the reasons for Kesler being there are interrupted by Mark's other friend Josh (Dan Hill) complaining about the 'Under shout.'

43.title: No Turning Back
43.plot: Undercover Cop Munroe (Daniel Hill) unexpectedly shows up at his handler Carl's (Ben Grimshaw) house to discuss the case.

44.title: Facing Reality
44.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a recovered junkie who returns to his old Dealer (Isaac Still), conflicted by his past and the challenge of staying clean he tries to walk the line between both worlds.

45.title: Trouble in Paradise
45.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who comes home to a problematic relationship that is on the rocks as his partner (Michelle Raw) and him argue about their future together.

46.title: I'll Send You a Call
46.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man rocking up late to his first date with a girl (Laura Vine) who isn't exactly everything she seems..

47.title: The New Employee
47.plot: Daniel Hill stars as an overconfident man who eyes off the new girl (Michelle Raw) at work.

48.title: Losing Faith
48.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man questioning the validity of his religion as he assesses the injustices prevalent around him.

49.title: The Secret
49.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a young man wanting to share a secret with his best friend (Michelle Raw).

50.title: Coming Out
50.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man struggling to come to terms with his sexuality in a small country town as he fights with his boyfriend (Dushan Philips) about the secrecy of their relationship.

51.title: The Slasher
51.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a serial killer on the run filming a video confession.

52.title: A Macbeth Moment
52.plot: Daniel Hill stars as an understudy in a production of Macbeth, who subtly undermines the confidence of the lead actor (Dushan Philips).

53.title: High Standards
53.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a young man experiencing weed for the first time with his friend (Michelle Raw).

54.title: Wrong Man for the Job
54.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a young mob enforcer tasked with the challenge of performing a hit on his best friend Paulie by his demanding and controlling boss Marty.

55.title: Infertility
55.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man reluctant to give up on impregnating his partner (Seon Williams) despite countless doctors telling him he is unable to.

56.title: The Waiter Cuts Lunch
56.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man going on a blind date with an exciting new love interest (Tritia DeVi Sha) but is constantly interrupted by a musical waiter (Lazurus Aureus) who takes an interest in his lady companion.

57.title: Grandfather Knows Best
57.plot: Dan Hill stars as a man visiting his grandfather (John Allan) in an effort to restore his former happiness.

58.title: I Need Your Help
58.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man who is ambushed by a strange request from his best friend (Seon Williams)

59.title: Fresh Out of Prison
59.plot: Daniel Hill stars as a man fresh out of prison going to visit his friend (Ava Lumiere) whom he blames for his incarceration.

60.title: The Con Artist
60.plot: A con artist (Dan Hill) tries to worm his way out of a criminal conviction by attempting to gain leverage over the prosecutor of his case (Melissa Langley).

61.title: Going to War
61.plot: A young soldier (Dan Hill) tries to break the news of his impending departure to his Father (Kostas Makrygian) who disapproves of his Military Service.

62.title: Sleazy Micky
62.plot: The sleazy Mick (Dan Hill) puts on a bet with his mate that he can easily seduce his new housemate (Sabeena Manalis).

63.title: Retribution: Part 2
63.plot: A man (Dan Hill) finally tracks down the perpetrator (Paul Broadby) responsible for the death of the love of his life and seeks to impose his own justice on the individual.

64.title: Uncle Nico
64.plot: A young Greek man (Dan Hill) has turned his back on his culture and embraced that of the laid back Aussie one, much to the disappointment of his Uncle Nico (Kostas Makrygian).

65.title: Reunion
65.plot: A young man (Dan Hill) is confronted by his long lost adopted brother (Roger Wilson) who he hasn't seen for 10 years. His brother tries desperately to reach out to him knowing he doesn't have much time left.

66.title: Multicultural Minute
66.plot: An obnoxious reporter (Dan Hill) interviews a Bollywood Starlet Priya Singh (Celina Lazarus) and clearly forgets his place.

67.title: Friends with No Benefits
67.plot: A man whose concern for his friend Kate has put a strain on their relationship as he becomes judgmental of her choices.

68.title: Full Cream Goodness
68.plot: An uptight man (Dan Hill) whines to his chilled out roommate (Ariel Simone) that the house isn't up to his lofty standards.

69.title: Special Friends
69.plot: A man with a disability (Dan Hill) sulks in his little hideaway as someone close to him (Tamsin Khor) tries to convince him to leave.

70.title: Frankie Don't Dance
70.plot: Frankie (Dan Hill) gets conned to come over by his best friends wife (Tamsin Khor) so she can tell him to stop coming around so regularly..

71.title: Forgiveness
71.plot: A brother (Dan Hill) thinks he owes his dead father some respect but when he takes his sister (Ariel Simone) to the cemetery, tensions rise when they remember the person he was.

72.title: Just J
72.plot: A publicist and fan boy (Dan Hill) of Jet, (Xander Speight) who is a leading man and new teen sensation, sets up a meeting to do the unfortunate part of his job and keep his public image at its best.

73.title: Inheritance
73.plot: The adopted brother Jonathan (Dan Hill) couldn't be more different to his brother David (Tasker Streete) who seems to have had his life handed to him for years. However, when their father passes away, Jonathan feels this his father may have left him something to turn his luck around.

74.title: Too Organised
74.plot: A nervous boy tries to awkwardly talk to his girlfriend about being more overtly sexual with him.

75.title: The Missing Shotgun
75.plot: Josh (Dan Hill) is a troubled child who doesn't know how to handle his problems. His father (Jason Deane) reaches out to him to try to connect..

76.title: Your Head and Your Heart
76.plot: Two best friends (Mike Lister + Dan Hill) reminisce about the past as they recap an event that changed their lives but taught them that friendship lasts forever.

77.title: One Mistake Too Many
77.plot: When a man who has lost his way (Dan Hill) returns to his favourite spot when he was younger, his brother (Xander Speight) confronts him and tries his best to convince him to come home.

78.title: Gambling Everything for Love
78.plot: A man (Dan Hill) seeks the blessing of his girlfriends father Mr Bartrand (Roger Dray), for his daughters hand in marriage.

79.title: Outcast
79.plot: An outcast brother (Dan Hill) visits his sister (Kate Greer) for a favour on a very touchy subject.. As always the unpredictable brother is quickly judged considering his shady unspoken history.

80.title: The Break In
80.plot: When a robber (Dan Hill) finds the location of a modern artifact he is keen to get his hands on it. However are the obstacles in his way too much to handle?

81.title: The David v Goliath Charity Rematch
81.plot: Wrestling is a business and they need to sell as many tickets as they can. So pro wrestlers David (Dan Hill) and Goliath (Mohamed Ali Vaez) stage a press conference promoting their next bout in the ring.

82.title: Death's Tender Embrace
82.plot: A mysterious stranger (Dan Hill) appears to a young and innocent girl called Abby (Ellie Bricknell). What transpires is proof that there is a degree of humanity in all beings.

83.title: More Than He Bargained For
83.plot: A slithering real estate agent (Dan Hill) prepares for his day of sales only to be put in a situation he would never have expected by a young lady (Emily Payne).

84.title: Wildlife Documentary Footage
84.plot: Documentary filmmakers Dan and Tim travel to the Balnarring Wildlife reserve to see a wide range of native Australian flora and fauna.

85.title: RIP Beautiful Doris O'Brien
85.plot: A tribute to a beautiful woman that passed in late 2015 - Doris O'Brien. To a beautiful grandmother, mother, wife and friend.

86.title: Curtains Closing
86.plot: A comedian (Rod Smith) ponders his past glory when his son Dylan (Dan Hill) informs him there's still a chance.

87.title: Benny's Back
87.plot: After a series of viral big brother auditions, the notorious Benny Kirkright (Dan Hill) decides that the only show intense enough to handle him is 'The Bachelor'.

88.title: Jake Fights for His Job
88.plot: Jake (Dan Hill) builds up the courage to confront his boss Darren (Roger Dray) about getting his job back. Only the circumstances for the conversation could be better..

89.title: The Girlfriend
89.plot: Brendan (Dan Hill) uses every opportunity to make his sister April (Cindel Waddington) look stupid. However, when April finally meets his girlfriend she may just have something to hold over him.

90.title: The Talent Advisor
90.plot: When Henry hears his obnoxious and unprofessional employee Ricky has a major issue, he decides to use the opportunity to bring attention to his unorthodox methods.

91.title: Home Is Where the Heart Isn't
91.plot: Aaron (Dan Hill) has always got an agenda. When he tries to take advantage of his loving mother (Loraine Fabb), he realises he may have just gone too far..

92.title: The Girl with the Blond Hair
92.plot: Two strangers Scott and Abbey can't hide their attraction to each other after a few random encounters. Their exchanges can't be avoided when they finally meet and have the chance to talk at the bus stop.

93.title: You Broke a Beautiful Thing
93.plot: The rich businessman Tony (Dan Hill) organizes an informal meeting with his favourite girl Felicity, (Jacinda Rose) to discuss work and her relationship with a client named Peter Philips.

94.title: A Game Between Gentlemen
94.plot: Mr Polanski (Karl Peschek) challenges his worker Damian (Dan Hill) to a friendly game of tennis. White line fever soon sets in as the two decide to spice it up with a high stakes bet..

95.title: 28 Minutes Later
95.plot: A scared boy Adam Braysen (Dan Hill) picks up his friend Jonesy (Nader Sajjadi-Emami) after the world starts acting strange.

96.title: Haggard & McCormack
96.plot: The Baron (Jay Bardon) is a drug kingpin that rules the Miami region. A 'party animal' Billy Bo (Dan Hill) approaches the Baron to buy some of his product.

97.title: You Will Not Make a Noise
97.plot: Private Jacobson (Dan Hill) washes and folds the clothes of his superior officer (Scott Marrinan) and finds himself in a dire situation when the officer insists on a new form of payment.

98.title: Long Lost Brothers
98.plot: Two brothers, Zack (Dan Hill) and Toby (Kieran Gould) are on the run from some shady individuals. Before leaving town they stop at a lake to try and clear the air between them.

99.title: Back from War
99.plot: Michael (Dan Hill) returns home from his tour of the Middle East; unfortunately, he brings home the memories of what happened. Once worried they would have lost him to enemy fire, his family now fears that they may have lost him to his mind.
